Gbenga Odogun, Lokoja The Kogi state Independent Electoral Commission has fixed the Local government election for December 12. The Chairman of the SIEC, Maman Eri, made the announcement at a stakeholders meeting on Wednesday in Lokoja. Eri said the fixing of the date was in line with the state governmentâ€™s decision to conduct free, fair and credible elections to fill the political positions of the chairmen and councillors in all the 21 local government areas of the state. Copyright PUNCH.
